    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2390</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-31T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KAAM1">Admiral Knight</persName> telegraphs Bolsheviks won
                    control in city election. Department desires information concerning causes of
                    this, part played by rivalry of autonomous Siberian and <persName
                        corresp="#p_HGDL1">Horvat</persName> governments and by pro-German elements,
                    and effect on local situation. Who is Czecho-Slovak commander? Department
                    desires further information concerning Czecho-Slovak request for assistance
                    Japanese torpedo boats at Nikolaevsk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
